# RMS Architecture

This file is the **layer map**: which directory holds what, who depends on whom. Domain invariants (sync, auth, photo, IDs, time) live in `conventions.mdc`. The Hybrid Plan model lives in `hybrid-plan-model.mdc`. Do not duplicate them here.

## 1. Monorepo topology

```
apps/api/                    Go backend (chi + huma v2 + sqlc + pgx + goose)
apps/web/                    React SPA (Vite + TanStack Router + Zustand + Tailwind v4 + shadcn/ui + openapi-typescript types)
packages/api-contracts/      OpenAPI as source of truth + generated TS types
docs/knowledge/              locked architectural decisions (read before editing)
docs/planning/               sprint scope and stack decision history
```

Additional client: mobile `rms_mobile/` (separate repo) consumes the same `openapi.yaml`. Any OpenAPI break = break for two clients.

## 2. `apps/api` layers

| Directory | What lives here | What does NOT |
|---|---|---|
| `cmd/api/` | `main.go`: wiring (config ‚Üí db ‚Üí sync ‚Üí middleware ‚Üí handler.Register), server startup | business logic |
| `internal/config/` | env config, sole source of truth for `os.Getenv` | hardcoded values |
| `internal/db/` | **generated by sqlc** | manual edits forbidden |
| `internal/sync/` | sync protocol DTOs (`PushOperation`, `PullChange`, payload types) | SQL, http, other domain logic |
| `internal/jwtutil/` | issue/parse JWT, claims struct | authorization checks, reading token from `*http.Request` |
| `internal/middleware/` | chi middleware: auth (extracts `workspaceId` into context), logging | huma wrappers |
| `internal/handler/<domain>/` | huma handlers for one domain + `Register(api huma.API)` | inline SQL, direct `pgx.Conn`, other domain logic |
| `queries/<entity>.sql` | sqlc queries for one entity | multi-domain SELECT via JOIN for convenience |
| `migrations/001_init.sql` | full schema (sprint 1 ‚Äî one file) | new `002_*.sql` before release |

Layer rule: handler ‚Üí (sync DTOs) ‚Üí sqlc Queries. Handler never calls `pgx` directly and never builds SQL. Handlers accept `db.Querier`, not `*db.Queries` (see ADR-0002).

## 3. `apps/web` layers

| Directory | What lives here |
|---|---|
| `src/api/` | HTTP wrappers (`fetch`) with types from `packages/api-contracts/types.gen.ts` |
| `src/stores/` | Zustand stores ‚Äî shared state across pages (e.g. auth + persist) |
| `src/pages/` | screens mounted by TanStack Router routes |
| `src/components/` | feature and reusable components (thin) |
| `src/components/ui/` | shadcn/ui primitives |
| `src/layouts/` | route shells (`Outlet`) |
| `src/router.tsx` | route tree (code-based TanStack Router) |
| `src/styles/` | global CSS, Tailwind `@import` and `@theme` |

All API calls go through `src/api/client.ts`. Bypassing this layer is a bug.

